questionTemplates.text:
M: Mary, would you join me for dinner tonight?
W: You treated me last weekend. Now, it's my turn. Shall we try something Italian?
{a}

M: You ought to see a doctor about the cough.
W: I guess I should. I've not taken it serious.
{a}

M: Hello, may I speak to Hong Li, please?
W: Oh, hold on a second, I'll check for you.
{a}

M: If you can make up your mind about the color, I can start on the outside of your house early next week.
W: Well, right now I think I want white for the window frames and yellow for the walls, but I'll let you know tomorrow.
{a}

W: That was such an interesting movie! I hope you enjoy it as much as I did.
M: I must admit that I fell asleep after the first thirty minutes.
{a}

M: I'd like to pick this film up by four tomorrow afternoon.
W: I can have it for you at two if you like.
{a}

F: Does your father smoke?
M: No, but he used to smoke.
{a}

F: You mustn't touch the wet paint, Bill.
M: I'm sorry. I won't do it again.
{a}

W: I heard you received the top grade on all five exams this semester.
M: Only on four, I'm afraid.
{a}

M: What would you like to have, Madam?
W: Well, I'd like to have a cup of coffee and a chicken sandwich.
{a}

W: You seem to have a lot of work to do at your office. You're always staying late and working overtime.
M: That's true. But it's no bother to me. The work is interesting. I don't mind extra hours at all.
{a}

M: I'd like a white dress please, one without collar and belt.
W: This one might suit you, Madam. Try it on please.
{a}

M: If I go to the store, will you make dinner for us tonight?
W: Bring back enough food.
{a}

F: Your presentation is well done.
M: Thank you, teacher.
{a}

W: Where have you been all this time? The train is about to leave!
M: Sorry I'm late, but I was waiting for you at the information desk upstairs. It's lucky I thought to look for you here on the platform.
{a}

M: You look quite different from what you used to.
W: Sure. I started exercising regularly two years ago and went from 253 pounds to a healthy 160 pounds and that is the only thing I did not give up halfway.
{a}

W: Have you bought a new camera again? You're turning my flat into a camera museum!
M: I'll stop. I'll try. But I probably can't. I see a new model and my knees go weak!
{a}

W: Where is the salad I made this morning?
M: We ate it, mom. Can you make more for us?
{a}

W: I want a ticket to London, please. Second class.
M: Single or return?
{a}

M: Can I bring you anything from the shop?
W: Get me 3 kilos of apples.
{a}

W: Would you mind if I borrow your English workbook?
M: Not at all. But please give it back before dinner so that I can take it to class this evening.
{a}

M: How do you come to the new house?
W: I come to there by bus.
{a}

W: The map shows that this street goes downtown.
M: Yes, but what we want to know is how to get to the park.
{a}

W: You'd better take an umbrella with you. It looks like it's going to rain.
M: You may be right.
{a}
